<Author>Singapore_traveler
<Content>Best 5* hotel in Singapore I鈥檝e stayed here for +/- 15 nights over a one month period (November) whilst moving house and I can鈥檛 say anything other than that I was not sure I was happy once I found a new place. What a fantastic hotel with superb staff and service. This is in my opinion the best you can get in Singapore at the moment. I have stayed at the Fullerton and Ritz Carlton before and had dinner/brunch at many more 5* hotels, but the St. Regis definitely beats them all!Rooms: beautifully furnished and complete with all of today鈥檚 luxuries/requirements. The flat screen TV comes complete with Bose sound system and off course there is a DVD player. The bed is truly wonderful (I have to find out where I can buy one myself) and the sheets and linen are of fantastic crisp quality. It was difficult for me to get out of bed every time! The bathroom is stunning with a free standing tub and built-in flat screen TV in the facing mirror and a marble shower with full length heated mirrors. Naturally there are plenty of towels and the likes and toiletries are of the highest quality (if you stay in a suite you even get a nice face wash 飦?.FB: I have only tried Les Saveurs and can鈥檛 comment on the other restaurants although I did notice the Mediterranean restaurant was mostly empty at night. At Les Saveurs the b-fast is just right. I am not a big fan of huge buffets where everything is always of mediocre quality and towards the end it looks like a bunch of starved soldiers paid it a visit. At St. Regis there is a decent buffet with high quality produce, such as nice fresh fruits and berries, good breads and pastries, some cold cuts and smoked salmon and off course orange juice etc. Other (hot) b-fast items, such as omelets/pancakes/full English etc., can be ordered 脿 la carte and are included in the price. For dinner the restaurant is ok, not special. I had one dinner that was great when there was a visiting chef but the other time is was just ok. Not really worth the price if you know what else is out there in Singapore. The wine list is really good and the sommelier is a very nice chap that knows his wines. Last but not least; Sunday brunch is a clear winner again. Every 5* property in SG tries to lure you with their all-inclusive Sunday champagne brunches but the St. Regis really does the job. It is a mix of buffet and 脿 la carte and they also walk around with 鈥渂ite size鈥?delicacies such as caviar, foi gras etc. The whole setup makes for a much more pleasant experience where you can really enjoy the company of your other diners as well.Service; what you would expect from a top 5* hotel. Everyone goes out of their way to make you feel at home. The butler service is nice and so is the complementary tea and coffee service.Others: Spa is beautiful (I did not try any treatments so can鈥檛 comment) and the steam bath/sauna is great to relax. Every evening there is a small complementary wine tasting which is enjoyable but nothing more. I found the wines quite ordinary and would have expected slightly better quality wines. 
