<Author>1stclassluxurytravel
<Content>What a let down!!! I totally agree with the previous reviewer..Something is just not right here???We were really looking forward to the end journey of our European leg to unwind for 5 nights at the St Regis..But it was a continual process of errors and problems and a real let down.The Hotel itself is New and beautiful, and incredible chandeliersand decor throughout.. but for a wonderful stay this hotel needs to sort out its electrical problems.. we had lights that didnt work, the tv in the bathroom wouldnt change channels, the aircon would sporadically go on and off, they did have an engineer lookat the problem however it continued not to work effectively..The butler(s) were lovely but it would have been nice to have our own kettle to make a cup of tea or coffee as opposed to have to call everytime we wanted one.. It just felt uncomfortable to have to continually call them, and an intrusion into our privacy..There is 101 switches near the side tables that we just gave up on trying to turn lights on, lights off, back light, hall light, it was just over the top and frustrating to keep on trying to get it right..We found the bed rather a little to firm for our liking and were amazed that there was no options for pillows.. I like a large pillow but my husband doesnt and ended up with a very sore neck after 5 nights..The staff were gracious, however on 4 different occassions we asked questions to staff to be greeted with I am from china ??The staff themselves were lovely and tried very hard to be polite but had no understanding of any english, this was both in the Ya Ting restaurant when we asked for another bottle of wine and in our suite when they came for a turn down service and we asked what time tomorrows newspaper would be delivered.. Hmmm?The spa facilities were lovely but lacked a certain vibe, actually there was a complete lack of ambience throughout the entire hotel, one could attribute that to the current low occupancy, but not in this case, we have been to many newly opened hotels and there always seemed to be some energy and excitement, but not here..The food at Le saveurs was very reasonably priced and the breakfast was possibly there best service, food of a very high standard.. Also the staff here were excellent. Overall I would recommend certainly booking a table at one of the restaurants at the St regis, but check in somewhere else..The Ritz and Conrad are much more dated then this beautiful New hotel, but they consistently get it right..We have never left either of those hotels nor the Fullerton with such a lack lustre experience.. 
