<Content>Need to work out service problems My wife and I stayed for four days at the recently opened hotel during the Easter weekend. I was initially impressed with the welcome I received at the hotel, from the welcoming doormen, reception and the butler. I was looking forward to the level of service for which St. Regis is renowned for. Unfortunately, the service that I was getting was not as detailed as advertised. In fact, it was in the details that they failed to fulfill my expectation. I found my room temperature very hot when we were checking in, there were masking tapes marking spots that needed touch ups on the ceiling and the carpet was a bit dirty.When I complained, I was taken very seriously and I was given an upgrade. Unfortunately that was not the end of my problems. Again they failed to impress me with their low attention to details such as my room was not made up at 3 PM even after I pressed the 'make up room' button at 11 AM.The hotel is a nice change for me in the often mechanically efficient Singapore. I like the personal touch such as the hotel managers approaching guests and having small talks as they were having breakfast. I accept that the hotel is new, but they should work out their housekeeping management immediately before their reputation goes down.I can be a fussy guest, especially when I am paying top dollars at a property like this one. That is why I am rating my stay as okay. 
