<Author>TokyoBoris
<Content>Opulent, but still working out kinks in service Stayed 10 nights at the St. Regis Singapore, about 6 weeks after the hotel opened for business. Arrived at 2am and was escorted to the room by 3 staff (!) - the manager, porter, and the butler. Room was large  beautiful, with flowers changed daily, fresh fruit delivered every evening, great views of the city, very comfortable bed  furniture. Bathroom is spacious and well equipped. Butler is at your beck  call 24 hours a day and brings press pot coffee (complimentary) any time you need it. Gym is well-equipped and not at all crowded.Restaurants were all good - the French and Chinese restaurants are elegant and the service deliberately slow-paced (figure on spending 2-3 hours for dinner). The Mediterranean restaurant by the pool offers a more casual environment and faster-paced service. While the hotel is a fantastic place to stay, it is still in startup mode with gaps in service noticeable from time to time. One example was a room service dinner - I placed our order and was told 30 to 35 minutes for delivery; the food did not show up for 90, and it was barely warm by that time. On top of that, the butler and the room service manager offered different explanations for the delay, adding to the feeling that things are not quite running like clockwork yet. With that said, I would recommend the St. Regis to travelers who are looking for high-end accommodations in Singapore. I expect the service issues to be resolved over time. 
